<h1 id="propose-special-depreciation">Propose special depreciation</h1>


<p>In Japan, a special depreciation is permitted under certain conditions. For Reserve method, this is a two step task: post reserve, and then post reserve allocation. For Direct-off method, only one step is needed, which is the same procedure as post reserve.</p>
<p>Use this procedure to learn how to propose special depreciation under Reserve method.</p>
<p>Make sure that the fixed asset has been acquired before following this procedure. Also, be sure that the Fixed Assets configuration key is selected.</p>
<p>This procedure uses the JPMF demo company data.</p>
<h2 id="post-reserve">Post Reserve</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Fixed assets &gt; Journal entries &gt; Fixed assets journal.</li>
<li>Click New.</li>
<li>In the Name field, type a value.</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
<li>Click Lines.</li>
<li>Click Proposals.</li>
<li>Click Extraordinary depreciation proposal.</li>
<li>In the To date field, enter a date.</li>
<li>Click Filter.</li>
<li>In the Criteria field, type a value.</li>
<li>Click OK.</li>
<li>Click OK.</li>
<li>Click Post.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="post-reserve-allocation">Post Reserve allocation</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Fixed assets &gt; Journal entries &gt; Fixed assets journal.</li>
<li>Click New.</li>
<li>In the Name field, type a value.</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
<li>Click Lines.</li>
<li>Click Proposals.</li>
<li>Click Extraordinary depreciation proposal.</li>
<li>In the To date field, enter a date.
<ul>
<li>Depending on the Allocation start convention, the Reserve allocation start date is different.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Click Filter.</li>
<li>In the Criteria field, type a value.</li>
<li>Click OK.</li>
<li>Click OK.</li>
<li>Click Post.</li>
</ol>
</article>
